1.17.0:
By placing a block against the top of an Amethyst Shard, regardless of its size, and subsequently removing the supporting block, the shard will remain floating in mid-air. Once it is floating, you can also remove the other block

In this version, when a dispenser is used to place powder snow on the right side of a portal (specifically East or North facing portals), the portal will split, leaving behind portal blocks solely on the layer where the snow was placed. This enables the removal of all obsidian blocks except for the ones on that particular layer

When mining a lit Observer, it will retain its lit state in the inventory. It's important to note that these lit Observers can be stacked with regular Observers

Paintings can overlap with Glow Item Frames, Signs, Banners, and Torches
Vindicators can spawn from Patrols when the world difficulty is set to Hard. However, this feature was removed later on, resulting in Vindicator Patrol followers and Patrol Captains being discontinued

You can place the following support blocks onto Lightning Rods: Torches, Snow layers, Buttons, Levers, Corals, Scaffolding, Bells, Rails, Tripwire Hooks, Repeaters, Comparators, Redstone Dust, Doors, Pointed Dripstone, Twisting Vines, Vines, Ladders, and Glow Lichen. However, please note that Torches, Tripwire Hooks, Vines, Ladders, and Glow Lichen can only be placed on the side of the Lightning Rod

Big Dripleaf does not have any placement restrictions and can be placed on any block

Glow Lichen can be placed on farmland and dirt paths

Hanging Roots can be Waterlogged

When you tie an axolotl to a Fence or a Wall and then scoop it up, the Leashes will not detach from the Fences or Walls. As a result, the Axolotls will remain unattached and unable to be leashed

Using Dispensers to remove water from Bubble Columns does not destroy the Bubble Column itself; instead, it simply removes the water and reverts it to a non-waterlogged state. This can also be used to make flowing waterlogged bubble columns

Leashing Axolotls before scooping them up with a bucket will not unleash the axolotl

When a mob is left with only one heart and is simultaneously struck by an Instant Health Potion and an Instant Damage Potion, the mob becomes invincible. If the mob appears red and shaking, rejoining the game will restore its normal appearance
<br>


1.17.10:
!!!   PDV: End Portals give fall damage based on the player's y coordinate in the Overworld. y=75 is enough to kill an unarmored player and y=100 is enough to kill anyone!   !!!
When you waterlog stairs or slabs and subsequently break them, the water does not update, resulting in floating water

Dripleaf blocks can be cut off by mineshafts, resulting in floating Dripleaf Stems within the Mineshafts. This occurrence is extremely rare due to the specific conditions required for it to happen. The Dripleaf must generate on the same x and z coordinates as the Mineshaft and at a specific height where the top portion of the Dripleaf gets cut off. If you wish to observe this yourself, you can enter the seed -1970066601 and go to the coordinates: -266 7 -253

Previously loaded chunks will get 64 bedrock layers if you turn on the "Caves and Cliffs" Experimental Toggle

Support Blocks can be placed onto Candles

Placing and picking up a Banner makes it Unstackable with crafted Banners
Picking up a Fish, or any other mob that can be scooped up, right as it dies, gives you a dead animal in a Bucket

By surrounding lava or water with portal blocks on all sides and then updating the portals by placing blocks next to them, you have the ability to create floating lava or water. This technique can also be applied to gravity blocks such as sand or gravel

in the end dimension, if you place an end crystal and then 2 pistons on different sides with their heads facing the end crystal, and activate them both at the same, they both will extend, leaving 2 piston heads in the same block

Putting something on fire and breaking the block underneath while the game setting "Fire Spreads" is off will make the fire float and it won't distinguish. To see floating fire, you can use the discontinued feature tweaks texture pack
