1.18.30:
!!!   PDV: World sizes may fluctuate. They can randomly increase exponentially, resulting in Worlds with gigabytes of junk data   !!!
All types of Torches, redstone dust, Glow Lichen and Walls can be placed or attached to Bells
In this version, you can use the regen dupe. Blocks placed and broken in any dimension can reappear in glitched states upon re-entering the dimension or relogging. In order for this to work, following requirements must be met: It must be in the East or the West, it must be the lowest subchunk (higher subchunks won't work) and the subchunk must be completely empty. This allows us to create half-beds, invisible shulker boxes, headless pistons, lit redstone components, wall skulls, etc. Once all of the requirements are met, you must place the blocks you wanna turn into glitched blocks, relog or switch dimensions, go back and break all the blocks, relog or switch again and when going back again they should be back in a glitched/invisible state. Some things even drop themselves if you were to break them such as wall skulls. Wall skulls have different variants depending on how you place the skulls down. Placing down a skull on the ground will give you a Wither Skeleton Wall Skull, but placing them connected to a wall facing certain cardinal directions gives you other variants. West gives you a Creeper Wall Skull, South gives you a Steve Wall Skull, North gives you a Zombie Wall Skull and East gives you a Dragon Wall Skull. Note: The different wall skull variations stack with each other and placing them down will turn them into Skeleton Skulls
<br>
